view.net\/forum?id=6Kg26g1quR\">Paper<\/a><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Adaptive Proximal Gradient Method for Convex Optimization<\/strong><br><a href=\"https:\/\/neurips.cc\/virtual\/2024\/poster\/93476\">Poster<\/a> | <a href=\"https:\/\/openreview.net\/forum?id=qlH21Ig1IC\">Paper<\/a><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Functional Bilevel Optimization for Machine Learning<\/strong><br><a href=\"https:\/\/neurips.cc\/virtual\/2024\/poster\/94248\">Poster<\/a> | <a href=\"https:\/\/openreview.net\/forum?id=enlxHLwwFf\">Paper<\/a><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>First-Order Minimax Bilevel Optimization<\/strong><br><a href=\"https:\/\/neurips.cc\/virtual\/2024\/poster\/95895\">Poster<\/a> | <a href=\"https:\/\/openreview.net\/forum?id=GZoAUVSkaw\">Paper<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ol>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Optimization was one of the top five topics at NeurIPS 2024, reflecting a clear trend of increasing interest in this area compared to previous years. While optimization in machine learning often focuses on specific tasks like training neural networks (using algorithms such as gradient descent and its variants), my focus here is on <\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":148,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_coblocks_attr":"","_coblocks_dimensions":"","_coblocks_responsive_height":"","_coblocks_accordion_ie_support":"","footnotes":""},"categories":[],"tags":[19,18,17,15,8,16],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"http:\/\/mahdimostajab.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/146"}],"collection":[{"href":"http:\/\/mahdimostajab.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"http:\/\/mahdimostajab.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/mahdimostajab.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/mahdimostajab.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=146"}],"version-history":[{"count":3,"href":"http:\/\/mahdimostajab.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/p